File: docs/content/docs/sdk/prompts.mdx

The definePrompt function signature at lines 24-27 references TypedPromptConfig<TArgs> but this interface is never defined on the page. The actual interface from platform/plugin-sdk/src/index.ts lines 140-146 is:

export interface TypedPromptConfig<TArgs extends z.ZodObject<z.ZodRawShape>> {
  name: string;
  description?: string;
  args: TArgs;
  arguments?: PromptArgument[];
  render(args: z.infer<TArgs>): Promise<PromptMessage[]>;
}

Add a new section after the definePrompt signature block (after line 28) showing this interface definition with a brief description. Follow the same pattern used for PromptDefinition (code block + properties table). The key difference from PromptDefinition is that render() receives z.infer<TArgs> instead of Record<string, string>.

Do NOT add a full properties table — a code block with the interface definition and a one-line description is sufficient since the properties are the same as PromptDefinition except for the render() parameter type.
